article.headline: Army 75, SUNY Maritime 59
article.story: WEST POINT, N.Y. (AP) -- Colin Harris and Matt Bell each scored 18 points to lead Army over New York Maritime 75-59 Thursday night. Bell scored all 10 of his first-half points in the last four minutes to help the Black Knights (2-6) build a 33-24 halftime lead. Army used a 25-10 run to make the score 58-34 midway through the second half. Cory Sinning added 10 points, six rebounds, five assists and two steals for the Black Knights. Robert Benton, who scored Maritime's first 12 points, had 24 points and 10 rebounds. No other Privateers (0-7) scored in double figures.
